AGI - "In previous overtime crises we have given Member States an extra tax margin by activating the safeguard clause. In short, we have given the Member States the power to substantially increase public investment linked to the crisis. I think we are now in another crisis that justifies a similar approach. That is why I can announce that I will propose to activate the safeguard clause for defence investment." The President of the European Commission, Ursula von der Leyen, said this in his speech at the Munich Security Conference.
&nbsp;
"This will allow Member States to substantially increase their defence spending. Of course, we will do it in a controlled and conditioned way. We will also propose a wider package of instruments tailored to the specific situation of each of our Member States. From their current level of defence spending to their fiscal situation," he added.
&nbsp;
"Second, for a massive defence package we also need a European approach to defining our investment priorities. This will allow investments in defence projects that are so necessary for common European interest," he said.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2 The note of Palazzo Chigi: "Good ad von der Leyen"</h2>
"The Italian Government welcomes with satisfaction the announcement of the President of the European Commission concerning new initiatives aimed at increasing investments in the defence sector, starting - as required by Italy - from the exclusion of such expenses from the Stabilita Pact". So we read in a note of Palazzo Chigi.
&nbsp;
"This is a first, fundamental step in the right direction - we still read in the note - that must be followed also by the establishment of common financial instruments. The Italian Government is ready to work constructively with the European institutions and with the other Member States in order to achieve these important objectives together, starting from the next presentation of the White Paper on EU defence".
